<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>PADSquad Data Automation Case Study | Kelly Boudreaux</title>
    <meta name="description" content="From spreadsheet chaos to client intelligence: architecting automated reporting for high-impact ad tech">
    <script type="module">
        import mermaid from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/mermaid@11/dist/mermaid.esm.min.mjs';
        mermaid.initialize({
            startOnLoad: true,
            theme: 'base',
            themeVariables: {
                primaryColor: '#1e40af',
                primaryTextColor: '#fff',
                primaryBorderColor: '#1e3a8a',
                lineColor: '#3b82f6',
                secondaryColor: '#60a5fa',
                tertiaryColor: '#dbeafe'
            }
        });
    </script>
</head>
<body class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-900">

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900 via-blue-800 to-blue-900 text-white py-20">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
            <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-300 mb-4">CASE STUDY</div>
            <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6 leading-tight">
                From Spreadsheet Chaos<br/>to Client Intelligence
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-blue-100 mb-8 max-w-3xl">
                Architecting automated campaign reporting for PADSquad:
                how to unify fragmented client data, eliminate manual processing,
                and deliver branded insights at scale.
            </p>
            <div class="flex gap-4 text-sm">
                <div class="bg-blue-800/50 px-4 py-2 rounded">
                    <div class="text-blue-300">Industry</div>
                    <div class="font-semibold">Ad Tech / Programmatic Media</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-800/50 px-4 py-2 rounded">
                    <div class="text-blue-300">Challenge</div>
                    <div class="font-semibold">Multi-Client Data Integration</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-blue-800/50 px-4 py-2 rounded">
                    <div class="text-blue-300">Solution</div>
                    <div class="font-semibold">Enterprise ETL + AI Normalization</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Problem -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">The Problem</h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    PADSquad serves enterprise clients like Home Depot, McDonald's, and Toyota with high-impact
                    display and video advertising across CTV, mobile, and desktop. Each client delivers campaign
                    performance data in different formats: Excel spreadsheets via email, CSV files with custom
                    field names, Google Sheets links with varying metric structures.
                </p>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    Account managers spend hours manually cleaning, normalizing, and transforming this data
                    before they can generate client-ready reports. The process is repetitive, error-prone,
                    and pulls their focus away from strategic client work.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-12">
                <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6">
                    <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">15+ hrs/week</div>
                    <div class="text-gray-700">per account manager on manual data processing</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6">
                    <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">3-5 days</div>
                    <div class="text-gray-700">turnaround time for client reports</div>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6">
                    <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-2">Zero</div>
                    <div class="text-gray-700">standardization across client data sources</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Three Client Scenarios -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Three Clients, Three Data Formats</h2>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <!-- Home Depot -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="bg-orange-600 text-white px-6 py-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Home Depot</h3>
                        <div class="text-sm text-orange-100">Retail</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">DATA FORMAT</div>
                        <div class="mb-4">Excel spreadsheet (.xlsx) via email</div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">FIELD NAMING</div>
                        <div class="font-mono text-xs bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded mb-4">
                            "Total Impressions"<br/>
                            "Click Through Rate"<br/>
                            "Video Completion %"<br/>
                            "Media Spend"
                        </div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">CHALLENGE</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-700">Multiple sheets per file, aggregated weekly data with subtotals</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- McDonald's -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="bg-red-600 text-white px-6 py-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">McDonald's</h3>
                        <div class="text-sm text-red-100">QSR / Restaurant</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">DATA FORMAT</div>
                        <div class="mb-4">CSV file (.csv) via SFTP</div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">FIELD NAMING</div>
                        <div class="font-mono text-xs bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded mb-4">
                            "imps"<br/>
                            "ctr_pct"<br/>
                            "viewability_rate"<br/>
                            "total_cost_usd"
                        </div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">CHALLENGE</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-700">Daily data, abbreviated field names, multiple campaigns per file</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Toyota -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="bg-red-700 text-white px-6 py-4">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold">Toyota</h3>
                        <div class="text-sm text-red-100">Automotive</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="p-6">
                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">DATA FORMAT</div>
                        <div class="mb-4">Google Sheets (shared link)</div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">FIELD NAMING</div>
                        <div class="font-mono text-xs bg-gray-50 p-3 rounded mb-4">
                            "Served_Impressions"<br/>
                            "CTR"<br/>
                            "VCR_Percent"<br/>
                            "Investment"
                        </div>

                        <div class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 mb-2">CHALLENGE</div>
                        <div class="text-sm text-gray-700">Real-time updates, inconsistent date formatting, mixed aggregation levels</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-8 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6">
                <div class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">The Pattern</div>
                <div class="text-gray-700">
                    Every client delivers the same core metrics (impressions, CTR, viewability, spend),
                    but field names, formats, and delivery methods are completely inconsistent. Manual
                    normalization is the bottleneck.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Architecture Solution -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">The Solution: Enterprise ETL + AI Normalization</h2>

            <div class="mb-12">
                <div class="mermaid">
graph LR
    A[Home Depot<br/>Excel Email] --> D[Salesforce<br/>Email-to-Case]
    B[McDonald's<br/>CSV SFTP] --> D
    C[Toyota<br/>Google Sheets] --> D
    D --> E[Tableau Prep<br/>Builder]
    E --> F[AI Normalization<br/>Einstein/Claude API]
    F --> G[Salesforce<br/>Campaign Performance Object]
    G --> H[Tableau Dashboard<br/>PADSquad Branded]
    H --> I[Automated PDF<br/>Report Generation]
    I --> J[Account Manager<br/>Notification]

    style D fill:#0176d3,color:#fff
    style E fill:#e8912d,color:#fff
    style F fill:#1e40af,color:#fff
    style G fill:#0176d3,color:#fff
    style H fill:#e8912d,color:#fff
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How It Works</h3>
                <ol class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
                    <li>
                        <strong>Data Ingestion:</strong> Client data arrives via Salesforce Email-to-Case (Excel attachments),
                        SFTP monitoring (CSV files), or Google Sheets API connection. All three paths funnel into Salesforce.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>ETL Processing:</strong> Tableau Prep Builder automatically detects new data, runs pre-configured
                        flows to clean and shape each client's format (removing subtotals, standardizing date formats, handling nulls).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>AI-Powered Normalization:</strong> Einstein AI or Claude API (via Salesforce Apex callout) maps
                        inconsistent field names to standardized schema. "Total Impressions" / "imps" / "Served_Impressions" all
                        become <code>Impressions__c</code>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Single Source of Truth:</strong> Normalized data writes to Salesforce Custom Object
                        <code>Campaign_Performance__c</code> with standardized fields across all clients.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Automated Reporting:</strong> Tableau dashboard pulls from Salesforce object, applies PADSquad
                        branding, and exports to PDF on schedule (or on-demand).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>Notification:</strong> Salesforce Flow sends email or Chatter notification to account manager
                        when report is ready.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Tech Stack Breakdown -->
    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Tech Stack: Leveraging Existing Infrastructure</h2>

            <div class="bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-6 mb-8">
                <div class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Strategic Decision</div>
                <div class="text-gray-700">
                    This architecture uses 95% of PADSquad's existing Salesforce and Tableau stack.
                    The only new component is the AI layer for intelligent field mapping. Minimal change management,
                    maximum leverage of tools the team already knows.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="space-y-6">
                <!-- Salesforce -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-blue-600 text-white p-3 rounded">
                            <svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path d="M12 2C6.48 2 2 6.48 2 12s4.48 10 10 10 10-4.48 10-10S17.52 2 12 2zm0 18c-4.41 0-8-3.59-8-8s3.59-8 8-8 8 3.59 8 8-3.59 8-8 8z"/>
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Salesforce (Existing)</h3>
                            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Data Ingestion + SSOT</div>
                            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
                                <li><strong>Email-to-Case:</strong> Automatically captures client data sent via email attachments</li>
                                <li><strong>Custom Object (Campaign_Performance__c):</strong> Standardized schema for all client data</li>
                                <li><strong>Salesforce Flow:</strong> Orchestrates Tableau Prep triggers and account manager notifications</li>
                                <li><strong>No new licenses required</strong> - uses existing Salesforce infrastructure</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Tableau -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-orange-500 text-white p-3 rounded">
                            <svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path d="M3 13h8V3H3v10zm0 8h8v-6H3v6zm10 0h8V11h-8v10zm0-18v6h8V3h-8z"/>
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Tableau (Existing)</h3>
                            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">ETL + Reporting</div>
                            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
                                <li><strong>Tableau Prep Builder:</strong> Cleans and shapes data from three different client formats</li>
                                <li><strong>Tableau Prep Conductor:</strong> Schedules automated flow runs, no manual triggering</li>
                                <li><strong>Tableau Dashboard:</strong> Pre-built PADSquad-branded template with client metrics</li>
                                <li><strong>PDF Export:</strong> Automated generation of client-ready reports on schedule</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- AI Layer -->
                <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 border-2 border-blue-500">
                    <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
                        <div class="bg-blue-900 text-white p-3 rounded">
                            <svg class="w-8 h-8" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                                <path d="M9 3L5 7h3v6H5l4 4 4-4h-3V7h3L9 3zm11 11h-3V8h3l-4-4-4 4h3v6h-3l4 4 4-4z"/>
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex-1">
                            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">AI Normalization Layer (New)</h3>
                            <div class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-3">Intelligent Field Mapping</div>
                            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
                                <li><strong>Einstein AI or Claude API:</strong> Maps inconsistent field names to standardized schema</li>
                                <li><strong>Salesforce Apex Callout:</strong> Triggers AI normalization within existing Salesforce flow</li>
                                <li><strong>Learning System:</strong> Improves mapping accuracy over time as new clients are added</li>
                                <li><strong>This is the only new component</strong> - everything else already exists at PADSquad</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Sample Report -->
